<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 8:04PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN SURRY...EAST
CENTRAL WILKES AND NORTHWESTERN YADKIN COUNTIES THROUGH 830 PM EDT...
At 804 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Clingman, or over Ronda, moving northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Elkin...
Jonesville...
Boonville...
Ronda...
Benham...
Pleasant Hill...
and State Road.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
